JOB DESCRIPTION
Reporting to the Director, Corporate Services, the Information Technology Manager is responsible for leading the planning and implementation of best-in-class Information Technology activities to support the HKSI’s elite sport and corporate operation needs. Leading the IT Department team, the IT Manger is responsible for the following:
Working collaboratively across the organisation to lead the identification, implementation, monitoring and maintenance of all the HKSI’s information and communications technology systems within both short and long term planning frameworks;
To regularly review and recommend the most up-to-date application, content and computing platforms to enhance the HKSI’s elite sport and corporate operations data processing and analytic needs;
To lead the evaluation, and guide strategic provisioning of applicable technologies to ensure elite sport and corporate systems are interoperable and align with both elite sport and corporate administrative data needs;
To direct the future oriented development, implementation monitoring and maintenance  of a highly secure, efficient and cost-effective IT infrastructure including hardware, software and storage systems;
To ensure a dynamic comprehensive risk-management strategy is in place including disaster recovery plans, and security systems to reduce vulnerabilities such as data leakages etc;
To regularly review, enhance, and/or introduce as necessary all IT related policies and procedures and to monitor compliance;
To ensure timely and effective technical support, help desk services to all user departments; and
Perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.
 THE REQUIREMENTS

A university degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or a relevant disciplines; A Post graduate degree is preferred;
A minimum of 10 years’ Management experience in a similar role;
Excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese. Ability to speak Putonghua is a definite advantage;
Strong communication and presentation skills.  Excellent interpersonal skill in dealing with all levels of staff across the organisation;
Highly motivated individual, who places emphasis on teamwork and has excellent strategic thinking and analytical skills.
APPLICATIONS
Please send the completed application form with indication of your current and expected salary to The Human Resources Manager, Hong Kong Sports Institute Ltd, 25 Yuen Wo Road, Sha Tin, New Territories or email: hrdept @ hksi.org.hk on or before 30 January 2022. Please quote reference no. JD-20220117-ITM in the application.
Appointment will be on a fixed term contract. General information is available at the website http://www.hksi.org.hk.
Applicants who are not invited for interview within six months may consider their applications unsuccessful.
All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence. Data collected will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purposes only.
THE HKSI IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Responsibilities: 

Manage and lead the planning and implementation of IT technical projects (e.g. Cloud implementation, IT infrastructure projects);
Manage project schedule, resources and risks. Perform proper escalation to ensure project success;
Ensure all the contractual commitments and deliverable are successfully delivered by vendors on time and within the budget;
Conduct system analysis, implementation, testing, user training and documentation on IT systems;
Interface with customers on system implementation for business systems projects;
Perform product evaluation, vendor selection, and procurement of IT solutions / products. 

Requirement:

Degree in IT/ Computer Sciences/ Computer Engineering or related discipline
5 years solid experience in IT project management with technical knowledge;
Certified in any PMP, Agile, or Scrum Master is preferred
Key competencies:
Leading others 
Composure
Interpersonal Savvy 
Business Acumen
Dealing with Ambiguity

We offer competitive salary package and career development opportunity.  Free company coach is provided. Interested parties, please quote our reference number and apply with full resume, present and expected salary, by clicking "APPLY NOW". 


We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for consideration of your application for the relevant post within the HGC Global Communications Limited. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly according to our Personal Information Collection Statement, a copy of which will be available upon written request. Information of unsuccessful candidates will be destroyed within six months.

Requirements:
Degree holder in Computing, Information Technology, Electronic Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics or related disciplines;

At least 10 years of relevant working experience in the banking industry, with at least 5 years in IT management or system operation aspect;

Hands on experience in system operation role;

Sound knowledge in the operation on systems, data center, network, information security and etc.

Good experience in open platform, network, SAN/NAS/network;

Good communication skill and project implementation capability with high self-motivation

With qualification of CCNA/CCNP/CCIE/MCSE will be an added advantage;

Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.

(Candidate with less experience will be considered as Information Technology Manager.)

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit .

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.

The Job

The MPFA has been tasked by the Government to design, develop and operate a digital platform, eMPF Platform, to standardize, streamline and automate the existing MPF scheme administration processes.  Through the adoption of new technologies and innovative solution, this user-centric platform will bring about revolutionary change to the MPF ecosystem, thus creating further room for scheme administration fee reduction to benefit all MPF scheme members.  On 5 March 2021, the eMPF Platform Company Limited was established as MPFA’s wholly owned subsidiary to take forward the eMPF Platform project.  For background and details of the eMPF Platform project, please go to our website https://www.mpfa.org.hk/en/empf/overview.

The appointee will support the development and implementation of an oversight programme in relation to overseeing the operation of the eMPF Platform to safeguard system integrity and stability.  The appointee will also be involved in key projects with a view to supervising the performance of functions assigned to the eMPF Platform Company Limited and the system readiness of MPF trustees for on-boarding the eMPF Platform.  The main responsibilities include:

To support the development of an oversight framework which would effectively oversee and supervise the operation of the eMPF platform to safeguard system integrity and stability;
To assist in establishing and enforcing standards and sound practices for and communicate compliance expectations with the eMPF Platform Company Limited;
To collaborate with the eMPF Platform Company Limited and oversee its performance of operational functions delivered either directly or through outsourced vendors;
To collaborate with eMPF Platform Company Limited to ensure that the eMPF Platform would adopt appropriate technical security measures and proper safeguards to protect the system security and data;
To perform evaluation of control design and carry out assessment of the effectiveness of internal controls and risk management concerning eMPF operation processes, IT systems, cyber security and system resilience;
To support projects at the MPFA level on reforms of MPF system, supervision of MPF trustees in relation to their system readiness for on-boarding the eMPF Platform, and other related initiatives; and
To perform other duties as assigned.

The Person

A recognized degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business or related disciplines;
At least eight years of relevant experience in regulatory compliance, retirement schemes / pensions, system auditing, cyber security or technology risk management, of which at least four years should be at supervisory level, preferably gained from sizable or public organizations;
Possess certifications such as CISA, CRISC or other relevant qualifications;
Strong knowledge and understanding of the business strategies, challenges and risks in MPF operation and technology project management;
Strong analytical skills and ability to effectively prioritize and coordinate multiple deliverables simultaneously;
Effective negotiator and communicator; and
Excellent interpersonal, leadership and influencing skills, self-motivated, solutions oriented and able to work under pressure.

Remuneration Package

A competitive remuneration and benefits package including a discretionary performance-linked variable pay, annual leave, medical, dental and life insurance coverage, and MPF will be offered.  The appointment will be made on a fixed-term contract for two years with the possibility of renewal of the appointment, subject to operational needs and staff performance.

To Apply

Interested candidates are invited to apply by sending full career details and application letter, quoting the job reference number, with information of current / expected remuneration, availability, to the address below or by clicking the "Apply Now" button:

Human Resources Department, MPFA

Level 8, Tower 1, Kowloon Commerce Centre

51 Kwai Cheong Road, Kwai Chung, Hong Kong

The closing date for application is 28 January 2022 or postmarked on 28 January 2022.  Applicants not invited for interview by the end of March 2022 may assume that their applications are unsuccessful and their applications will not be retained for more than two years.

The information provided will be kept confidential and only be used for those purposes relating to your application.  Please visit our website for the details of the MPFA’s Personal Information Collection Statement for Job Applicants at https://www.mpfa.org.hk/en/mpfa/joining-mpfa/job-vacancies/personal-information-collection-statement.  The MPFA is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates.

Assistant Information Security Manager / Senior Information Security Officer – Information Technology Services Centre (Ref: AISM / SISO (ITSC) 2022-01-14)

(Ref: AISM / SISO (ITSC) 2022-01-14)



Responsibilities:

review and update security documents such as policies and guidelines;
assess risks on applications, systems, networks and adopt security measures in a balance manner for risk mitigation;
audit and run tests on systems and infrastructure to identity possible issues;
ensure digital assets adequately protected, effectively monitored and managed;
provide latest updates on information security to general users to increase their awareness; and
explore suitable information security technologies that can better safeguard the information in the university.

Applicants should:

possess a recognised bachelor’s degree or above in Computer Science or related discipline;
possess updated and relevant qualifications such as CISM, CISSP, CEH, ISO27001;
preferably have at least 10 years of relevant work experience;
have proven records in information security and system auditing in application, networks and system level;
have good interpersonal, communication, analytical and problem-solving skills;
have good command of written and spoken English and Chinese; and
be pleasant with positive mindset, good customer sense and willing to learn new technologies.

The appointee will be required to work during non-office hours.  Work experience in the higher education sector will be an advantage.  Applicants with fewer years of experience could be considered as Senior Information Security Officer. 


Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Interested applicant should visit this link https://recruit.hsu.edu.hk/ and apply on or before 30 January 2022.  The University reserves the right not to fill the position in this exercise.

Applicants who are not invited to an interview within three months may consider their applications unsuccessful.  All information received will be treated in strict confidence, and the data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.  The Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request.

the Hang Seng University of Hong Kong, incorporated in Hong Kong with limited liability by guarantee, is an equal opportunity employer.

Key Responsibilities

Responsible for growing the cybersecurity program and evolving the Group's transition to a mature secure and operational robust environment;
Provide day to day services delivery, infrastructure architecture & operate excellence improvement program;
Ensure the IT strategy for infrastructure and security requirements support the business growth and strategy;
Implement and oversee the deployment of information security and IT infrastructure technologies;
Develop and implement business continuity plans, security best practice, threat intelligence, and incident response;
Drive a continuing program of engagement to ensure everyone in the company is part of our cybersecurity defense;
Lead the technical infrastructure & support services team to deliver best-in-class technology services & minimize the risk of cyber-attacks;
Assist Associate Director of Group Information System on developing the IT strategy for infrastructure and cybersecurity requirements.

Requirement

Degree in Computer Science / Computing in Information System / Data Science & Analytics or Digital / Technology or related discipline;
Appropriate industry-recognized security qualifications or equivalent;
More than 6-8 years' experience in technical infrastructure & services tear for developer & proven track record for successfully managing and implementing technical infrastructure projects;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese, including Mandarin;
Excellent communication skills to demonstrate clear interpretation and presentation of results to various stakeholders.

We offer long-term career prospect and competitive remuneration package to the appointed candidate. Please apply in confidence with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary to Group Human Resources Department

