Job Description and Responsibilities:
1. Act as a Team Lead to lead and supervise all network/IT/system project management work and server maintenance related business service, ensure that team members comply with the company project delivery framework and continually optimize it. Ensuring Project deliver in line with the contract and implemented according to the implementation plan, and take responsibility for achieving project objectives.
2. To lead and manage project team and subcontractors to resolve project issues throughout project implementation and ensure operational compliance of the project and its delivery in line with the company's management systems and regulations.
3. To plan and coordinate, clear division of roles, communicating, monitoring goals, coaching and motivating all members regularly and positively by knowledge transfer to team members via mentoring, workshop and etc. It is estimated team members will be 4 people.
4. Ensure stability of all the business lines in Hong Kong by developing a communication plan and managing communications to ensure customers alignment
5. Identify & mitigate all the network project and server maintenance case SLA risk
6. Conduct proper escalation of issues/risks where and when appropriate and required. Maintain direct and transparent communication with superiors, and maintain internal and external personnel to fully perform their duties
7. Review project progress, financial matters and performance metrics with management on a regular basis

Job Requirements:
1. Bachelor degree or above, major in computer, network engineering, communications, and management;
2. More than 2 years of project management experience and have managed network projects, familiar with the data center environment, such as cabinet placement, data communication/IT equipment, integrated wiring is preferred;
3. Experience in server operation and maintenance experience are bonus points;
4. Able to perform the work under high pressure with minimal guidedance, experience in remote project management is preferred, PMP certification is preferred;
5.Exhibit good leadership skills without prejudice, and be good at dealing with the shortcomings of team members;
6.Highly adhere to the company's goals, good crisis management skills to deal with the pressure from project challenges and achieve company goal;
7.Ability to influence and motivate cross-functional teams to deliver successful project outcomes.

About our client:

Our client is a MNC Manufacturing Group having offices in Hong Kong, China, Asia, UK and US.  Due to their continuous expansion and re-engineering & New coming Cloud projects, this role reports to the Group IT Director, opportunity to be promoted to Director Level.


Strong Enterprise Architecture and systems Roadmap

*TOGAF Certification is a MUST
Implemented large-scaled ERP Systems


Responsibilities:

Plans, organizes, coordinates, and directs the activities of IT EA/Solutions Service teams to initially establish sound enterprise architecture and systems roadmap; effectively deliver, deploy and review appropriate IT solutions;
In conjunction and collaboration with business units, plans and establishes an appropriate enterprise architecture and roadmap that align IT with business, articulates the business and applications, defining the information flow, and mapping the transition;
Establishes and maintains appropriate enterprise architectural framework, governance, and documentation;
Contributes to the formulation and implementation of IT strategies, policies, plans, programs, processes, guides and standards of the IT Department;
Recruits, selects,evaluates and motivate staff; assigns and reviews projects with project managers to determine work priorities and monitor progress and risks; ensures adherence to standards and procedures; identifies, recommends and initiates staff training and development;
Collaborates and works closely with other IT sections and Business Units to identify opportunities and initiatives to satisfy business requirements or enhance efficiency, and acts as a catalyst for innovation and change;
Contribute to the preparation of IT budget and monitoring of expenditures.
Requirements & Qualifications:

Bachelor Degree in Information Technology / Information Systems / Computing or relevant discipline, a relevant Higher Degree is preferred;
*TOGAF Certification is a MUST
Sound project management track record, PMI Certified is an advantage;
Practical experience on Agile development;
Knowledge and experience in Enterprise Architecture and SDLC methodology
Minimum 10 years’ experience in software development with minimum 6 years in managing systems developments and project management;
Knowledge and experience on large-scaled ERP System implementation (e.g. Oracle EBS and Microsoft Dynamics AX) and supply chain management, experience Manufacturing is a plus;
Fluent in English, Mandarin and Cantonese
Able to present complex ideas or situations to senior management in a clear, concise and precise;
Willing to initiate change in a challenging environment, able to deal with people at different levels;
Based in Hong Kong, with extensive travelling to South China on a regular basis, and travelling periodically to overseas factories;
Opportunity to be promoted to Director Level

